Pettyjohn, Wood & White, Inc.Trusted Investment Portfolio Management Advisors
 



 








 At Pettyjohn, Wood & White, we provide trusted professional guidance and advice in the management of investment portfolios for a select group of clients. Our success is driven by our extensive attention to detail in customizing client portfolios and the depth of our personal commitment in managing the totality of our clients’ financial affairs.






















Our Team 






















Pettyjohn, Wood & White, Inc.Trusted Investment Portfolio Management Advisors
Investment Professionals
 


John D. Doyle, Jr.
Chairman
John Doyle, former owner and President of The Pettyjohn Company and currently Chairman of the Board of Pettyjohn, Wood & White, has over 40 years of experience in the investment, trust and banking industries. He worked in the trust department for Central Fidelity Bank for 15 years. Mr. Doyle is a 1963 graduate of Notre Dame.  He is the former Chairman of the Region 2000 Business & Economic Development Alliance and currently serves on the board of the Lynchburg Regional Business Alliance.





Gorham B. “Bunny” Wood
President
Bunny Wood is a co-owner of Pettyjohn, Wood & White and has 25 years of experience in the financial services industry. Mr. Wood co-founded Wood & White Investment Advisors, L.L.C. along with Charlie White in 2002 and grew the firm to over $100 million in client assets under management, before merging Wood & White with The Pettyjohn Company in January of 2014. Prior to forming Wood & White, Mr. Wood spent nine years as an investment advisor and Vice President with Scott & Stringfellow, Inc. Prior to joining Scott & Stringfellow, he served as Vice President and Commercial Loan Officer with NationsBank Corporation for four years. A graduate of the University of Virginia, Mr. Wood is a member of the CFA Institute, the Richmond Society of Financial Analysts, and is a past president of the Lynchburg Estate Planning Council. Mr. Wood currently serves on the boards of Amazement Square, the YMCA of Central VA, the Lynchburg City Schools Education Foundation and Westminster Canterbury – Lynchburg.






Charles B. White, CFA
Secretary-Treasurer
Charlie White is a co-owner of Pettyjohn, Wood & White and has worked in the financial services industry for 20 years. Mr. White co-founded Wood & White Investment Advisors, L.L.C. along with Bunny Wood in 2002 and grew the firm to over $100 million in client assets under management, before merging Wood & White with The Pettyjohn Company in January of 2014 . Prior to forming Wood & White, Mr. White served as Portfolio Manager and Vice President with Bank of America Capital Management. He started his career in the investment business with the Lynchburg-based money management firm of Davidson & Garrard, Inc. Mr. White is a graduate of The College of William and Mary and holds the Chartered Financial Analyst designation. He is a member of the CFA Institute, the Richmond Society of Financial Analysts and is a past president of the Lynchburg Estate Planning Council. Mr. White currently serves on the boards of the Greater Lynchburg Community Trust, Spring Hill Cemetery and the Lynchburg Chapter of the Virginia Center for Inclusive Communities.




Brian K. Blankinship
Vice President
Brian Blankinship has over 30 years of experience in the investment, trust and banking industries. Prior to joining the firm in 2007, he worked for Wells Fargo Advisors and for BB&T’s Private Bank. A 1984 graduate of James Madison University, Mr. Blankinship is a member of the Lynchburg Estate Planning Council.




Thomas D. Gerhardt
Vice President
Tom Gerhardt has over 50 years of experience in the investment, trust and banking industries. Prior to joining the firm in 1998, he was a Vice President and Trust officer for Central Fidelity Bank for 36 years. Mr. Gerhardt attended Lynchburg College and currently serves as a trustee on the board of The Williams Home, Inc.




C. Shep Nowlin, III
Vice President
Shep Nowlin began his career in the investment industry with Wood & White Investment Advisors, L.L.C. in August of 2005. Mr. Nowlin is a 2002 graduate of the McIntire School of Commerce at the University of Virginia with a concentration in finance. After graduation, Mr. Nowlin played golf professionally for two years on the Golden Bear Golf Tour in Florida. Mr. Nowlin was also employed with Trenzech Corporation, a residential development firm. Mr. Nowlin has served as Treasurer on the boards of the Awareness Garden Foundation and CASA of Central Virginia.




James W. Poats
Vice President
Jim Poats, Portfolio Manager and Vice-President, will celebrate his 28th year with the firm this year and has 33 years of experience in the financial services industry. Prior to joining the firm, he worked for Wheat, First Securities, Inc. for 5 years. A 1975 graduate of The University of Virginia’s McIntire School of Commerce, Mr. Poats currently serves on the board of The Summit, The Center for Economic Education and is a trustee and board member of First Christian Church.


Support Staff

Tonya Fortune is an administrative assistant and has worked for the firm since 2005. Prior to joining the firm, Tonya worked for J.C. Bradford (now Stifel Nicolaus) as a mortgage specialist.

Anna Payne is an administrative assistant and has worked for the firm since its inception in 1978.

Melissa Powell is an administrative assistant and has worked for the firm since 2007. Prior to joining the firm, Melissa worked at Wells Fargo Advisors.

Cheryl Wade is an administrative assistant and has worked for the firm since 1986. Prior to joining the firm, she worked for J. C. Bradford (now Stifel Nicolaus) and for Central Fidelity Bank (now Wells Fargo).













The Firm 






















Pettyjohn, Wood & White, Inc.Trusted Investment Portfolio Management Advisors
The Firm
Clunet H. Pettyjohn, Jr.,founder of The Pettyjohn Company
Pettyjohn, Wood & White, Inc. is one of the oldest, independently owned registered investment advisory firms in central Virginia.
The firm was started as The Pettyjohn Company in 1978 by the late Clunet H. Pettyjohn, Jr. Upon Mr. Pettyjohn’s passing in 1988, John D. Doyle, Jr. and William N. Mays purchased the firm, leading the firm together and furthering Clunet Pettyjohn’s legacy of trusted advice and service for approximately 17 years. Mr. Mays redeemed his interest in October 2005, and Mr. Doyle continued as the sole owner and President of the firm for the following 7 years.
On December 31, 2012, The Pettyjohn Company was acquired by Gorham B. “Bunny” Wood and Charles B. White. Mr. Wood and Mr. White were the founding principals and owners of the Lynchburg-based investment advisory firm of Wood & White Investment Advisors, L.L.C. On January 31, 2014, the operations of Wood & White were merged into The Pettyjohn Company, Inc. and the combined firm was renamed Pettyjohn, Wood & White, Inc. Mr. Doyle continues with Pettyjohn, Wood & White today as the company’s Chairman and Mr. Mays continues to serve on the company’s board of directors.
Over the years, the firm has grown to include a staff of eleven experienced professionals managing over $420 million in client assets as of December 31, 2016. The firm’s team of investment professionals has over 200 years of combined experience in the investment, trust and banking industries. The firm specializes in customized portfolio management for individuals, families, retirement plans, trusts, estates, endowments, and foundations. Pettyjohn, Wood & White remains independent and is not affiliated with any brokerage firm, bank, money management firm, or any other financial institution.













