FY2018 EPS Estimates for General Mills, Inc. (GIS) Boosted by Gabelli


					Posted by Joanna Charbonneau on Jul 18th, 2017 // No Comments





General Mills, Inc. (NYSE:GIS) –  Gabelli lifted their FY2018 EPS estimates for shares of General Mills  in a research note issued on  Thursday. Gabelli analyst S. Donnelly now forecasts that the company will post earnings of $3.15 per share for the year, up from their prior estimate of $3.10. Gabelli also issued estimates for General Mills’ FY2020 earnings at $3.45 EPS and FY2021 earnings at $3.60 EPS. 


 Get General Mills Inc. alerts:



Several other equities analysts have also commented on GIS. Vetr upgraded shares of General Mills from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $58.98 price objective on the stock in a report on Monday, May 1st. Zacks Investment Research upgraded shares of General Mills from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Monday, March 27th. Royal Bank Of Canada decreased their price objective on shares of General Mills from $66.00 to $65.00 and set a “sector perform” rating on the stock in a report on Wednesday, March 22nd. Stifel Nicolaus lowered shares of General Mills from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating and decreased their price objective for the stock from $67.00 to $60.00 in a report on Wednesday, March 22nd. Finally, Sanford C. Bernstein lowered shares of General Mills from a “market perform” rating to an “underperform” rating and set a $52.00 price objective on the stock. in a report on Tuesday, March 21st. Seven analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, twelve have issued  a hold rating and two have assigned  a buy rating to the company. The stock presently has a consensus rating of “Hold” and an average price target of $59.93.
ILLEGAL ACTIVITY WARNING: “FY2018 EPS Estimates for General Mills, Inc. (GIS) Boosted by Gabelli” was originally  posted by Chaffey Breeze and is the sole property of of Chaffey Breeze. If you are accessing this story on another domain, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of US & international copyright & trademark legislation. The legal version of this story can be accessed at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/18/fy2018-eps-estimates-for-general-mills-inc-gis-boosted-by-gabelli.html. 





Shares of General Mills (GIS) traded down 0.656% during mid-day trading on Monday, reaching $53.795. 2,323,025 shares of the company’s stock traded hands. The company’s 50-day moving average price is $56.80 and its 200-day moving average price is $59.47. General Mills has a 12-month low of $53.24 and a 12-month high of $72.70. The stock has a market capitalization of $31.05 billion, a PE ratio of 19.421 and a beta of 0.61. 
General Mills (NYSE:GIS) last announced its quarterly earnings data on Wednesday, June 28th. The company reported $0.73 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.71 by $0.02. The business had revenue of $3.81 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $3.75 billion. General Mills had a net margin of 10.61% and a return on equity of 38.97%. The firm’s quarterly revenue was down 3.1% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter last year, the firm earned $0.66 earnings per share. 
The business also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Tuesday, August 1st. Investors of record on Monday, July 10th will be given a $0.49 dividend. This represents a $1.96 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 3.62%. This is an increase from General Mills’s previous quarterly dividend of $0.48. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Thursday, July 6th. General Mills’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is 70.76%. 
A number of hedge funds have recently modified their holdings of the company. Baltimore Washington Financial Advisors Inc. acquired a new stake in shares of  General Mills during the fourth quarter worth $15,491,000.  Lenox Wealth Advisors Inc. boosted its stake in  General Mills by 0.8% in the first quarter. Lenox Wealth Advisors Inc. now owns 1,818 shares of the company’s stock valued at $107,000 after buying an additional 14 shares during the period.  Cribstone Capital Management LLC boosted its stake in  General Mills by 275.6% in the first quarter. Cribstone Capital Management LLC now owns 2,017 shares of the company’s stock valued at $116,000 after buying an additional 1,480 shares during the period.  Commonwealth Financial Services LLC boosted its stake in  General Mills by 1,239.8% in the first quarter. Commonwealth Financial Services LLC now owns 2,224 shares of the company’s stock valued at $130,000 after buying an additional 2,058 shares during the period.  Finally, Hanson McClain Inc. boosted its stake in  General Mills by 1.5% in the first quarter. Hanson McClain Inc. now owns 2,346 shares of the company’s stock valued at $138,000 after buying an additional 35 shares during the period. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  70.40% of the company’s stock. 
About General Mills
General Mills, Inc is a manufacturer and marketer of branded consumer foods sold through retail stores. The Company is a supplier of branded and unbranded food products to the North American foodservice and commercial baking industries. The Company has three segments: U.S. Retail, International, and Convenience Stores and Foodservice. 







