Pettyjohn Wood & White Inc. Purchases 50 Shares of Kimberly-Clark Corporation (NYSE:KMB)

Posted by David Goldstein on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 

Pettyjohn Wood & White Inc. increased its position in shares of Kimberly-Clark Corporation (NYSE:KMB) by 0.2% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 20,245 shares of the company’s stock after buying an additional 50 shares during the period. Pettyjohn Wood & White Inc.’s holdings in Kimberly-Clark Corporation were worth $2,665,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Other hedge funds also recently modified their holdings of the company. Zions Bancorporation increased its position in Kimberly-Clark Corporation by 8.6% in the fourth quarter. Zions Bancorporation now owns 971 shares of the company’s stock worth $110,000 after buying an additional 77 shares during the last quarter. Acrospire Investment Management LLC boosted its stake in shares of Kimberly-Clark Corporation by 125.0% in the first quarter. Acrospire Investment Management LLC now owns 900 shares of the company’s stock worth $118,000 after buying an additional 500 shares during the period. Clean Yield Group purchased a new stake in shares of Kimberly-Clark Corporation during the first quarter worth about $145,000. Pinnacle Bank purchased a new stake in shares of Kimberly-Clark Corporation during the first quarter worth about $162,000. Finally, Advantage Investment Management LLC purchased a new stake in shares of Kimberly-Clark Corporation during the fourth quarter worth about $169,000. 70.03% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 




Kimberly-Clark Corporation (KMB) opened at 123.71 on Friday. The company has a market cap of $43.91 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 20.41 and a beta of 0.78. The company’s 50-day moving average is $128.81 and its 200 day moving average is $127.89. Kimberly-Clark Corporation has a 1-year low of $111.30 and a 1-year high of $136.21. 


 Get Kimberly-Clark Corporation alerts:



Kimberly-Clark Corporation (NYSE:KMB) last announced its quarterly earnings results on Monday, April 24th. The company reported $1.57 EPS for the quarter, topping the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $1.54 by $0.03. The business had revenue of $4.48 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $4.50 billion. Kimberly-Clark Corporation had a return on equity of 602.48% and a net margin of 11.99%. The business’s quarterly revenue was up .2% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period in the previous year, the firm earned $1.53 EPS. On average, equities analysts predict that Kimberly-Clark Corporation will post $6.27 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
